<div ana="b1" subtype="diplomatic" type="edition">
<p>ΜΑΡΟΥ<lb/>ΡΙWΝΙW</p>
</div>
<div ana="b1" subtype="transcription" type="edition">
<p>Μαρης<lb/>
<expan>
<abbr>
<supplied cert="low" reason="lost">Κυ</supplied>ρίων</abbr>
<ex>ος</ex>
</expan> Ἰω<supplied reason="lost">άννου</supplied>
</p>
</div>
<div ana="b1" type="translation">
<p>Of Mares Kyrion (son) of John</p>
</div>
<div ana="b1" type="commentary">
<p>If ΡΙΩΝ is taken as a fragment of the name Kyrion, the inscription then refers to
                    one man by both his Aramaic and his Greek name instead of to two men on a single
                    ossuary.</p>
</div>
